PROJECT LICENSE — PLACEHOLDER, NOT YET FINAL

FoundryX does not yet have a final open-source license. Until one is
selected and this file replaced with its full text, the project is
"All rights reserved" under default copyright law, which means:

  - You may READ the source for personal evaluation.
  - You may NOT redistribute, modify, or use it in production without
    explicit written permission from the copyright holder.
  - Inbound contributions cannot be accepted under a clean license
    until this file is replaced.

Recommended next steps — pick one, then replace this file with the
verbatim license text (no header other than what the license itself
specifies):

  - Apache License 2.0 (recommended for AI/ML projects; includes
    explicit patent grants, which matter when the codebase trains,
    serves, or shapes model behavior).
  - MIT License (simpler, broadest compatibility, no patent grant).
  - Business Source License 1.1 (BSL) if a future open-source release
    is planned under a time-delayed model, with a converter license
    to Apache-2.0 after the change-date.
  - Dual license (e.g., AGPL-3.0 + commercial) if the project
    intends to monetize hosted services.

When you replace this file:

  1. Drop the chosen license text verbatim, with its required header.
  2. Update the "License" section in README.md.
  3. Add SPDX-License-Identifier comments at the top of every source
     file (optional but recommended for unambiguous reuse).
  4. Open a PR titled "chore: adopt <LICENSE> license" and link it to
     an ADR in docs/adr/ explaining the choice.

Until then, this file is the project's license.